---
// src/pages/reflections.astro
import Layout from '../layout/layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Reflections — Yash Shah">
  <div class="reflections-wrap">

    <div class="page-header">
      <span class="section-label">Task 1a</span>
      <h1>Optik Consultancy <span>Reflection</span></h1>
      <!-- <p class="intro">
        A reflection on my internship experience, the lessons learned, and how
        it has shaped my identity as a software engineer.
      </p> -->
    </div>

    <div class="questions">

      <article class="question-card reveal visible">
        <span class="q-number">01</span>
        <div class="q-content">
          <h2>What were your expectations about your internship before you joined?</h2>
          <p>Before the internship, I expected to be assigned a low-skill project designed to cater to my
            lack of experience in a professional software environment. I also anticipated that I might not
            enjoy the experience, as the 9-to-5 commitment seemed questionable when many software
            roles offer hybrid or remote flexibility. Furthermore, I assumed that supervisors would
            constantly monitor my actions and that I would not be trusted with larger-scale,
            high-impact projects.</p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="question-card reveal delay-1 visible">
        <span class="q-number">02</span>
        <div class="q-content">
          <h2>What was the reality? How was it different from your expectations?</h2>
          <p>The internship was far more challenging and rewarding than I had anticipated. While I quickly
            adapted to the 9-to-5 schedule, the work itself was much more substantial: I was tasked with
            building a fully functional product with my team within a 12-week timeframe. Despite having
            never handled a full-stack project of this scale, I was grateful for the opportunity to deliver a
            complete product. Most surprisingly, I was given significant autonomy, as my supervisors and
            team leads trusted me to manage my own workload and meet deadlines independently.</p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="question-card reveal delay-2 visible">
        <span class="q-number">03</span>
        <div class="q-content">
          <h2>What lessons were the most important from your internship? Why were they important?</h2>
          <p>One of the most critical lessons was the significance of effective daily standups. While I had
            used them sparingly in university, seeing them integrated with project management tools like
            Jira and Trello in a professional setting showed me how they prevent tasks from being delayed
            without the team's knowledge. Additionally, I learned the importance of team accountability.
            By holding each other responsible for our specific tasks and actions, we were able to maintain
            momentum and successfully develop a functioning product as a cohesive unit.</p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="question-card reveal delay-3 visible">
        <span class="q-number">04</span>
        <div class="q-content">
          <h2>After your workplace experience, what would you say your value proposition would be to an employer? How can you demonstrate this?</h2>
          <p>My core value proposition is adaptability. I entered this internship with no prior experience in
            full-stack development or AI-RAG pipelines. Although the initial weeks were difficult as I
            learned to navigate client meetings and technical updates, I rapidly adjusted. I can demonstrate
            this adaptability through my record of opening and reviewing multiple pull requests, integrating
            client feedback regarding my professional manner, and receiving positive stakeholder reviews
            on the final code base.</p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="question-card reveal delay-4 visible">
        <span class="q-number">05</span>
        <div class="q-content">
          <h2>How did your internship influence the type of role in which you are interested?</h2>
          <p>The internship sparked a strong interest in AI development, specifically in prompt engineering
            and model enhancement. However, noticing that I did not have the opportunity to work directly
            on APIs or databases during this tenure, I have identified a new career goal: transitioning into
            Backend Development to master the architectural side of software. Furthermore, I am now
            interested in DevOps roles, as I am eager to learn the technicalities of how complex
            applications and websites are deployed and maintained in production.</p>
        </div>
      </article>

    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style lang="scss">
  // ── Page wrapper ──────────────────────────────
  .reflections-wrap {
    max-width: 860px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 80px 24px 100px;
  }

  // ── Page header ───────────────────────────────
  .page-header {
    margin-bottom: 64px;

    h1 {
      margin-bottom: 16px;

      span {
        color: var(--blue-primary);
      }
    }

    .intro {
      font-size: 1.05rem;
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      max-width: 600px;
      line-height: 1.75;
      margin-bottom: 0;
      text-align: center;
    }
  }

  // ── Question cards ────────────────────────────
  .questions {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 28px;
  }

  .question-card {
    display: grid;
    // number column | content column
    grid-template-columns: 56px 1fr;
    gap: 24px;
    background: var(--surface-2);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    padding: 32px;
    transition: border-color 0.3s ease, transform 0.3s ease;

    &:hover {
      border-color: var(--border-hover);
      transform: translateX(4px);
    }
  }

  // ── Question number ───────────────────────────
  .q-number {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--blue-primary);
    opacity: 0.5;
    line-height: 1;
    padding-top: 4px;
  }

  // ── Question content ──────────────────────────
  .q-content {
    h2 {
      font-size: 1.05rem;
      color: white;
      margin-bottom: 14px;
      line-height: 1.4;
      // slightly smaller than global h2 since these are Q&A headings
      font-size: clamp(0.95rem, 1.5vw, 1.1rem);
    }

    p {
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      line-height: 1.8;
      margin-bottom: 0;
    }
  }

  // ── Responsive ───────────────────────────────
  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .reflections-wrap {
      padding: 48px 20px 72px;
    }

    .question-card {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 12px;
      padding: 24px;
    }

    .q-number {
      font-size: 1rem;
    }
  }
</style>